body_html: Sounds like a half-updated version of TensorFlow. Could you try removing TensorFlow entirely (e.g. pip uninstall tf-nightly or whichever package is installed), making sure import tensorflow fails, then reinstalling?

body: Sounds like a half-updated version of TensorFlow. Could you try removing TensorFlow entirely (e.g. `pip uninstall tf-nightly` or whichever package is installed), making sure `import tensorflow` fails, then reinstalling?
